ZH: 1. 他被选为公司的候补董事。
EN: 1. He was chosen as the company's alternate director.

ZH: 2. 如果有人退缩，候补队员会顶替他们参加比赛。
EN: 2. If someone backs out, the substitute players will take their place in the match.

ZH: 3. 请提供你的候补联系方式以备不时之需。
EN: 3. Please provide your alternate contact information for emergency situations.

ZH: 4. 她被任命为领队候补。
EN: 4. She was appointed as the alternate team leader.

ZH: 5. 这个学生遗憾地成为考试的候补。
EN: 5. This student unfortunately became a backup for the exam.

ZH: 6. 她希望成为选秀节目的候补选手。
EN: 6. She hopes to become a standby player for the talent show.

ZH: 7. 我们向候补观众发放了门票。
EN: 7. We distributed tickets to the standby audience.

ZH: 8. 他一直在等候补车厢的座位。
EN: 8. He has been waiting for a seat in the standby carriage.

ZH: 9. 他们在候补名单的第一位。
EN: 9. They are at the top of the waiting list.

ZH: 10. 这位演员原本是候补角色，却意外得到主演机会。
EN: 10. This actor was originally a standby role but unexpectedly got the lead opportunity.

ZH: 11. 随着天气预报的改变，候补场地被启用了。
EN: 11. With the change in weather forecast, the backup venue was activated.

ZH: 12. 他被选为候补国家队成员。
EN: 12. He was selected as a substitute member of the national team.

ZH: 13. 他是候补的首选人选。
EN: 13. He is the first choice for a backup.

ZH: 14. 我们已经组织好了一个候补奖项的名单。
EN: 14. We have prepared a list of alternate awards.

ZH: 15. 他被列为候补清单的第二位。
EN: 15. He was listed as second on the standby list.

ZH: 16. 请向我提供候补人的资料。
EN: 16. Please provide me with the information of the substitute person.

ZH: 17. 她是候补参加国际会议的代表。
EN: 17. She is the alternate representative for the international conference.

ZH: 18. 如果有空位，请把我放入候补名单。
EN: 18. If there is a vacancy, please put me on the waiting list.

ZH: 19. 候补乘客将在有座位时被允许上飞机。
EN: 19. Standby passengers will be allowed on board when there are available seats.

ZH: 20. 他参加比赛的机会只是一个候补名额。
EN: 20. His chance to participate in the competition is just an alternate spot.
